Female
(
Figs 39–41
). Forewing length 
2.2–2.4 mm
; wingspan 
4.7–5.4 mm
(n = 5). Similar to male, but fore-wing with a distinctive, yellowish cream fascia. Genitalia (
Figs 153–157
) 
550–665 µm
long. Abdominal apex trun-cated, with short setae; Anterior and posterior apophyses equal in length; anterior apophyses bent inwardly (
Figs 153, 154
). Corpus bursae with two large, oval-shaped signa (
Figs 153, 154, 157
); one signum is slightly shorter (
Fig. 157
). Ductus spermathaecae with 3.5–4 coils and a tube-like vesicle (
Fig. 156
).
